section.section:
Every retail installment contract shall:
Be in writing in at least eight (8) point type;
Contain all the agreements of the parties;
Be signed by the retail buyer; and
Require a copy thereof to be furnished to the retail buyer at the time of the execution of the contract.

text.section:
The retail installment contract shall contain the following:
The cash sale price of the motor vehicle which is the subject matter of the retail installment sale;
The amount of the retail buyer's down payment, whether made in money or goods, or partly in money or partly in goods;
The difference between paragraphs (a) and (b) of this subsection;
Amount, if any, included for insurance and other benefits; and
Types of coverage and benefits;
Official fees as defined in KRS 190.090;
Any amounts eligible for inclusion in the cash sale price as defined in KRS 190.090 that the seller elects to separately itemize; and
Principal balance, which is the sum of paragraphs (c), (d), and (e) of this subsection.
